we have an issue with the grading method on course syllabi (on the portal), which is affecting the grading method field in FM.

steps.projectObjectiveStep: •	The grading method for each course is defined in the layout Options Class Types, in the field Class Types::Grading Method	•	When I create a new course in the layout classDetails, the field Sections::GradingMethodis automatically populated by looking at the above field, ClassTypes::Grading Method	•	The grading method from Sections::GradingMethod then shows up on the course syllabi (next to the heading Grading System) (https://portal.pacificrimcollege.com/syllabus_print.lasso)	•	But then, at some point, the field clears both on the syllabus and inSections::GradingMethod.  I think it is clearing when the instructor publishes their syllabi.  So, the field will be populated when they are working on their syllabus, but after they clickSave and Publish the field is now blank both on the syllabus and in FM Sections::Grading Method.  Thankfully, the field in Options Class Types does not clear, so for this semester I have been referring to it, filling out Sections::GradingMethod manually in FM (after the instructor publishes their syllabi), and then the portal syncs and the grading method appears on the syllabus.	•	What should happen is that the grading method goes from Sections::GradingMethod to the Grading System field on the syllabus (as it does), but then not disappear (as it is currently).  The only way to change the grading method on the syllabus should be to edit the field Sections::Grading Method for the specific course in FM. We made a change last year to restrict instructors from being able to change the grading method on their syllabus (they used to be able to edit that field with a drop-down menu on the portal, and now they can’t) and I think the above issue started happening at that time.

objectives.projectObjective: We have a layout Enrolles Class Sign-In that our admin team has to print for each individual acupuncture clinic at the beginning of each semester.  They access the layout (called a sign-in sheet) here: <<Class Enrolles>>//Enrollees
When they click this button, they get a printable layout with information from the particular clinic they are currently viewing. <<Reports Class>>//Reports//Class
they have to find each clinic individually and click this button <<line in the portal>> for each one in order to print all of the sign in sheets.

If we can, I would like to somehow make it so they only have to click one button to print (or save) all of the sign-in sheets (or find all of the clinics they’re looking for, and then click one button.)

For many of our reports, we have a (Found) option, which will print the same report for every found record, instead of just for the active record.  We don’t have that option for this particular layout, though.
It would make sense for them to access this option from the Reports section of FM, but I’m fine with it being somewhere in Classes instead, if that’s easier or more clear.
I would still like to keep the current button/function in case they want to access just one sign-in sheet.
